---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/header";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout>
    <Header client:load />
    <section class="pt-[161px] md:pt-[177px] pb-[169px] bg-[#1C1C1C] -mt-[950px] md:-mt-[105px] px-4">
        <div class="max-w-[1043px] mx-auto">
            <h1 class="text-[40px] md:text-[70px] font-[Barlow] font-bold text-white md:text-center">Privacy Policy</h1>
            <p class="pt-[20px] md:pt-[100px] font-light text-[16px] tracking-[1px] text-white italic">Last Updated: 10/01/2025</p>
            <p class="text-white text-[16px] font-light pt-[30px] md:pt-[80px]">Brain Vector Inc. ("Brain Vector," "we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, store, and protect your personal and emotional data when you access our website, platform, applications, and services (collectively, the "Services"). <br> <br> By using our Services, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.</p>
            <h2 class="text-[24px]  md:text-[30px] md:leading-[30px] text-white font-medium pt-[32px] md:pt-[88px]">1. Information We Collect</h2>
            <p class="text-white text-[16px] font-light pt-[20px]">We collect the following types of data:</p>
            <p class="text-white text-[16px] font-light pt-[20px]">a. Personal Information</p>
            <ul class="text-white list-disc text-[16px] leading-[22px] font-light! ml-[35px]">
                <li class="pt-[2px]">Name, email address, contact details</li>
                <li class="pt-[2px]">Organization, role or profession (if provided)</li>
                <li class="pt-[2px]">Account login credentials</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-white text-[16px] font-light pt-[20px]">b. Emotional & Cognitive Data</p>
            <ul class="text-white list-disc text-[16px] leading-[22px] font-light! ml-[35px]">
                <li class="pt-[2px]">Self-reported emotional states (via AI dialogue)</li>
                <li class="pt-[2px]">Response patterns and usage behaviors</li>
                <li class="pt-[2px]">Feedback and mood-tracking within the platform</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-white text-[16px] font-light pt-[20px]">c. Technical & Device Information</p>
            <ul class="text-white list-disc text-[16px] leading-[22px] font-light! ml-[35px]">
                <li class="pt-[2px]">Browser type, IP address, device identifiers</li>
                <li class="pt-[2px]">Usage logs, interaction timestamps, session duration</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-white text-[16px] font-light pt-[20px]">d. Biometric & Sensor Data (if applicable)</p>
            <ul class="text-white list-disc text-[16px] leading-[22px] font-light! ml-[35px]">
                <li class="pt-[2px]">EEG data (if using biosensor-integrated sessions)</li>
                <li class="pt-[2px]">Heart rate or stress response metrics (when authorized)</li>
            </ul>
            <h2 class="text-[24px] leading-[26px]  md:text-[30px] md:leading-[30px] text-white font-medium pt-[50px]">2. How We Use Your Data</h2>
            <p class="text-white text-[16px] font-light pt-[20px]">We use your data to:</p>
            <ul class="text-white list-disc text-[16px] leading-[22px] font-light! ml-[35px]">
                <li class="pt-[2px]">Deliver personalized experiences and session recommendations</li>
                <li class="pt-[2px]">Analyze emotional and cognitive trends to improve the platform</li>
                <li class="pt-[2px]">Ensure platform functionality, security, and user support</li>
                <li class="pt-[2px]">Comply with legal and regulatory requirements</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-white text-[16px] font-light">We do not sell your data to third parties.</p>
            <h2 class="text-[24px] leading-[26px]  md:text-[30px] md:leading-[30px] text-white font-medium pt-[50px]">3. Data Storage and Security</h2>
            <p class="text-white text-[16px] font-light pt-[20px]">We use encryption, secure cloud infrastructure, and access controls to protect your data. Emotional and biometric data are anonymized or pseudonymized when possible.<br><br> All data is stored on secure servers in compliance with applicable data protection laws, including GDPR (for EU users) and CCPA (for California residents).</p>
            <h2 class="text-[24px] leading-[26px]  md:text-[30px] md:leading-[30px] text-white font-medium pt-[50px]">4. Sharing of Information</h2>
            <p class="text-white text-[16px] font-light pt-[20px]">We only share data when:</p>
            <ul class="text-white list-disc text-[16px] leading-[22px] font-light! ml-[35px]">
                <li class="pt-[2px]">Required by law or legal process</li>
                <li class="pt-[2px]">Working with trusted service providers under strict confidentiality agreements</li>
                <li class="pt-[2px]">Collaborating with academic research institutions (with explicit consent and anonymization)</li>
            </ul>
            <h2 class="text-[24px] leading-[26px]  md:text-[30px] md:leading-[30px] text-white font-medium pt-[50px]">5. Your Rights</h2>
            <p class="text-white text-[16px] font-light pt-[20px]">Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the right to:</p>
            <ul class="text-white list-disc text-[16px] leading-[22px] font-light! ml-[35px]">
                <li class="pt-[2px]">Access, modify, or delete your personal data</li>
                <li class="pt-[2px]">Request a copy of your stored information</li>
                <li class="pt-[2px]">Object to data processing or withdraw consent at any time</li>
            </ul>
            <h2 class="text-[24px] leading-[26px]  md:text-[30px] md:leading-[30px] text-white font-medium pt-[50px]">6. Third-Party Services & Cookies</h2>
            <p class="text-white text-[16px] font-light pt-[20px]">We may use third-party analytics or tracking tools (e.g., Google Analytics) to monitor performance and usability. These services may use cookies or other identifiers. You can manage cookie settings in your browser.</p>
            <h2 class="text-[24px] leading-[26px]  md:text-[30px] md:leading-[30px] text-white font-medium pt-[50px]">7. Children’s Privacy</h2>
            <p class="text-white text-[16px] font-light pt-[20px]">Brain Vector is not intended for users under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect data from children. If you believe we have collected such data, please contact us immediately.</p>
            <h2 class="text-[24px] leading-[26px]  md:text-[30px] md:leading-[30px] text-white font-medium pt-[50px]">8. International Data Transfers</h2>
            <p class="text-white text-[16px] font-light pt-[20px]">If you are located outside the United States, your data may be transferred to and processed in the U.S. By using our services, you consent to this transfer.</p>
            <h2 class="text-[24px] leading-[26px]  md:text-[30px] md:leading-[30px] text-white font-medium pt-[50px]">9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p class="text-white text-[16px] font-light pt-[20px]">We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page, with the “Last Updated” date revised accordingly. Continued use of the Services after changes implies acceptance.</p>
            <h2 class="text-[24px] leading-[26px]  md:text-[30px] md:leading-[30px] text-white font-medium pt-[50px]">10. Contact Us</h2>
            <p class="text-white text-[16px] font-light pt-[20px]">If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please reach out:<br>
            [Insert Email Address]<br>
            [Insert Mailing Address]<br>
            www.brainvector.com.au</p>
        </div>
    </section>
    <Footer client:load />
</Layout>